    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SERONO'S PROFIT JUMPS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elizabeth Olson</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olson, Elizabeth</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Serono SA, Europe's biggest biotechnology company, reports 62.3 percent rise in net profit, to $209.9 million for first nine months (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Serono S.A., Europe's biggest biotechnology company, reported a 62.3 percent rise in net profit, to $209.9 million, for the first nine months. Strong sales of Rebif, a drug for multiple sclerosis, helped the company exceed analysts' expectations of a 50 percent profit increase. Serono said sales of Rebif reached $68.1 million, a record level, in the third quarter, and nine-month sales of the drug doubled to $179.7 million.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
